@node "improvements" "Improvements"

 I think that all you cool guys out there giving me suggestions about MADS deserve a little bit more credit, so here are the improvements you suggested!
 
 
  - "View Contents" was suggested by Pussums (Catie?), and a bloody good idea it was :)
  
  - "Use" That was suggested by a hell of a lot of people, so here it is at last!
  
  - It can now UUEncode / UUDecode (Suggested by phoenix_bbs)
  
  - It is now able to archive using the Zip format. (suggested by... well, me :)
  
@endnode

@node "goodies" "Goodies!"

 From now on, I shall be including a drawer of "Goodies" that will included in the MADS archive. These are the following goodies so far:
 
  - YAUU = Which stands for "Yet Another Useless Utility", which I wouldn't say is that useless. It's basically a file extracter (Competition for MADS ey? :) which works through Tool Types
  
  - MADS.AnimGIF = Advertisement for MADS which can be included on on Web Pages like the IBrowse and Voyager adverts. Check it out!
  
@endnode

@node "future" "The Future!"

 As of today, development of MADS will cease for a while. Well, in a sense it will anyway. Lets just say that a new version won't be coming out every two weeks as it's doing now.
 
 The reason to this is that I have decided to (once again) re-write MADS. It's been in development now for quite a while, and because of that, the code has got so messy that not even I can understand it hardly. This has also caused lots and lots of bugs, which would kinda be difficult to track down now. 
 
 Because of all the reasons above, I am going to re-write it, and this will talke me quite a few months.
 
 Some of the features that MADS 2.0 will include are the following:
 

 * Font Sensitive GUI (Happy RugbyHead? :)
 * Bug Free :)
 * Standard Progress Window with Progress Bar
 * Lha, Lzx, DMS, PKD, Zip, Base64, UUEncode Archivers
 * Lha, Lzx, DMS, PKD, Base64, UUDecode, UnTGZ, UnZip Extracters
 * On-Line Help
 * Catalog Enabled
 * Lovely MagicWB Spinning Logo for About Window
 * Auto Palette Detect, and Icon selection
 * Different Types of Icons
 * Normal, MagicWB and NewIcons Icons
 * Auto Resolution Detect, and Screen Opening if needed
 * PPDecrunch and CrMDecrunch Internally
 * Propper Icon names in DOpus 5.5+
 * No more "Uninitialized Window" or "GTList already attached" errors


 You can expect to see the first few ßeta versions coming out sometime near Christmas.
 
 If you have any contributions towards MADS (eg logos, Icons, Archivers, etc) the please oh please send them to @{"me" link "author" 0}!
@endnode
  